"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Aug 12, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104pfs1665702941848.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pfs1665702941848.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/pfs1665702941848.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"pfs1665702941848\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      LDAP\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online\n    directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and\n    maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web\n    servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pfs1665702941848__p_d51179e1_d51180e1_d51181e1\">LDAP runs directly over TCP/IP or TLS, and can be used to access a stand-alone LDAP directory service or to access a directory service that uses an X.500 standards-compliant database. A directory is similar to a database, but tends to contain more descriptive, attribute-based information. The information in a directory is generally read much more often than it is written.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"pfs1665702941848__p_d51182e1_d51183e1_d51184e1\">Uniface applications can connect to LDAP servers using the Uniface LDP connector. Using the LDAP V3 protocol, it can connect to LDAP servers, including stand-alone LDAP servers and X.500 Directory System Agents with an LDAP gateway installed.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bio1665702942630.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP Data Structure</a><p>LDAP data is stored in a record-like structure, called an entry. No table or field definition information is stored in the LDAP environment. Instead, each entry contains its own field definitions.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aif1665702663917.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Data Storage and Retrieval on LDAP</a><p>LDAP differs substantially in structure from traditional relational databases.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/eat1665702663987.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Map LDAP Entries to Uniface Entities</a><p>You cannot use the database import facility with LDAP, so you must manually define a model that maps LDAP entries to Uniface entities.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/hpa1665702942777.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Configure Uniface for LDAP</a><p>To configure Uniface to connect to with LDAP, you need to edit the Uniface application assignment file.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/mcs1665702735695.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>LDAP Connector</a><p>The Uniface LDAP connector enables you to connect with LDAP servers, including stand-alone LDAP servers and X.500 Directory System Agents with an LDAP gateway installed.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530898\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2530898\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "LDAP Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Aug 12, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 LDAP The Lghtweight Directory Access Protocol (LDAP) is a protocol for accessing online directory services. It offers common access to a centralized facility for storing and maintaining user access privilege, email, and sign-on information which can be shared among Web servers, mail servers, news servers and Uniface applications. LDAP runs directly over TCP/IP or TLS, and can be used to access a stand-alone LDAP directory service or to access a directory service that uses an X.500 standards-compliant database. A directory is similar to a database, but tends to contain more descriptive, attribute-based information. The information in a directory is generally read much more often than it is written. Uniface applications can connect to LDAP servers using the Uniface LDP connector. Using the LDAP V3 protocol, it can connect to LDAP servers, including stand-alone LDAP servers and X.500 Directory System Agents with an LDAP gateway installed. Related Links LDAP Data Structure LDAP data is stored in a record-like structure, called an entry. No table or field definition information is stored in the LDAP environment. Instead, each entry contains its own field definitions. Data Storage and Retrieval on LDAP LDAP differs substantially in structure from traditional relational databases. Map LDAP Entries to Uniface Entities You cannot use the database import facility with LDAP, so you must manually define a model that maps LDAP entries to Uniface entities. Configure Uniface for LDAP To configure Uniface to connect to with LDAP, you need to edit the Uniface application assignment file. LDAP Connector The Uniface LDAP connector enables you to connect with LDAP servers, including stand-alone LDAP servers and X.500 Directory System Agents with an LDAP gateway installed. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}